The patch has a payload on it.

Avast 5 did not detect this one (unlike the many other false positives it does).

The patch apparently does work, it looks like my copy was "patched", however, Avast was completely crippled after this.  I had to remove and reinstall it to correct this.

Dr Guard was installed.  Dr Guard is a fake malware protection program.  It not only disabled Avast, it disabled my firewall (win 7) and disabled my ability to remove it without resorting to malwarebytes and trojan remover and several reboots later.  

Dr Guard is an asshole related program.  Whoever wrote it to get you to buy that shit is an asshole.
